<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="234" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                        <head>234. Telegram 7 from Geneva to Hong Kong<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d234fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/9–2655. Official Use Only. Repeated to the Department of
                                State as telegram 775.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-26">September 26, 1955, 5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d234-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d234-1"/>
                        <p>7. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Nicholson, American Red Cross, would appreciate information from you
                            and/or Tomlin on whether American civilians recently released from
                            prison report having received packages transmitted at Hong Kong through
                            Red Cross channels.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName><hi rend="strong">Shillock</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>